comment: Morris (WAS) makes incidental contact with Clarkson (LAL) that does not affect his SQBR.
[Detectable with stop watch] Gortat (WAS) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Morris (WAS) makes contact with the ball after it has reached its apex and is on its downward flight toward the basket.
Morris (WAS) makes marginal contact with Russell (LAL) and does not affect his ability to defend the play.
Black (LAL) sets the screen on Wall (WAS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Wall (WAS) makes incidental contact with Black (LAL) that does not affect his SQBR.
Gortat (WAS) sets the screen on Black (LAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Williams (LAL) stops and changes directions and does not drive through Wall (WAS) on his move toward the basket.
LAL are assessed a delay of game following the timeout.
Morris (WAS) makes contact to Black's (LAL) arm that affects his shot attempt.
Black (LAL) sets the screen on Oubre Jr. (WAS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Oubre Jr. (WAS) makes incidental contact with Clarkson (LAL) that does not affect his FOM.
Wall (WAS) and Deng (LAL) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Black (LAL) and Beal (WAS) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Russell (LAL) commits the take foul on Wall (WAS).
Porter (WAS) makes incidental contact with Black (LAL) that does not affect his FOM.
Williams (LAL) makes contact to Wall's (WAS) arm that affects his SQBR.
